            <title>[SUREFIRE-685] Cannot pass multiple comma-separated includes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-685</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cannot pass multiple comma-separated includes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;as in&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;includes&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;include&amp;gt;*&lt;b&gt;/pattern.java,&lt;/b&gt;*/another.java&amp;lt;/include&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/includes&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is problematic because I was troubleshooting a build and injecting variable include values through ${} property and profiles and can no longer do so. Please reinstate this functionality, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
